Clinton Scott Nageotte [nuh-ZHOTT] (born October 25, 1980 in Parma, Ohio) is a right-handed pitcher who is currently a free agent. Nageotte was selected by the Seattle Mariners in the 5th round (155th overall) of the 1999 Major League Baseball Draft, and played parts of three seasons for the Mariners, from 2004 through 2006. He most recently played for the Somerset Patriots of the independent Atlantic League in 2009. He was a standout athlete at Brooklyn High School in Brooklyn, Ohio. He resides in New Port Richey, FL. 
